That explorer tendency has been a perfect match for working as a general pediatrician-- always something new to learn! 

It hasn't directly increased my range-- I am a soprano 2 with a 3 octave range-- but maybe it did help me get stronger in the chest register. Because it helps to start down there to have somewhere to go. I like the upper break too for something more subtle, such as the single jumps in Blue Bayou, but for a full blown country yodel, IMO the big contrast is more fun.

